# Netlify / Cloudflare Pages redirect rules.
#
# Both platforms auto-serve /404.html on a missing route without
# any config, but this file is the explicit declaration: anything
# unmatched falls through to /404.html and the HTTP response is
# returned with a real 404 status (not 200).  The trailing "404"
# is what flips the status code; without it, the platform serves
# the page content but with HTTP 200, which trips up SEO crawlers
# and breaks `curl -fsSL` scripts that rely on the status to
# detect broken links.
#
# Order matters — keep this rule LAST in the file so any
# legitimate /path rewrites above it match first.

/*    /404.html   404
